
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Science Connect Database

class Person {
  - personID: String (PK)
  - name: String
  - phoneNumber: String
  - keywords: List<String>
  - institutionCode: String (FK)
}

class ResearchInstitution {
  - institutionCode: String (PK)
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class ScientificArticle {
  - doi: String (PK)
  - title: String
  - authors: List<Person> (with position)
  - type: String ("peer-reviewed" or "technical report")
}

class PeerReviewedPaper <<interface>> {
  + citationCount: Integer
  + reviewers: List<Person>
}

class TechnicalReport <<interface>> {
  + publisherInstitution: ResearchInstitution
}

class Journal {
  - journalName: String
  - publisherName: String (FK)
  - impactFactor: Double
}

class Publisher {
  - publisherName: String (PK)
  - journals: List<Journal>
}

class Subscription {
  - researchInstitution: ResearchInstitution (FK)
  - journal: Journal (FK)
}

' Associations and Inheritance
ScientificArticle <|-- PeerReviewedPaper
ScientificArticle <|-- TechnicalReport

Person "1" -- "0..*" ScientificArticle : author of
Person "0..*" -- "0..*" ScientificArticle : reviewer of

ResearchInstitution "1" -- "0..*" TechnicalReport : publishes
ResearchInstitution "0..*" -- "0..*" Subscription : subscribes to

Publisher "1" -- "0..*" Journal : publishes
Journal "1" -- "0..*" Subscription : subscribed by

Person "1" -- "0..1" ResearchInstitution : works for
@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Person`**: Represents researchers. Each person is associated with one `ResearchInstitution`, and can be an author or reviewer of articles.
- **`ResearchInstitution`**: Stores information about EU institutions. They can publish technical reports and subscribe to journals.
- **`ScientificArticle`**: Base class for both `PeerReviewedPaper` and `TechnicalReport`. Each has a DOI, title, and list of authors with positions.
- **`PeerReviewedPaper`**: An interface that extends `ScientificArticle`. It includes citation count and reviewers.
- **`TechnicalReport`**: An interface that extends `ScientificArticle`. It includes the publisher institution.
- **`Publisher`**: Represents organizations like Elsevier or IEEE. They manage journals.
- **`Journal`**: A publication managed by a publisher. Journals have names and impact factors.
- **`Subscription`**: A link between a `ResearchInstitution` and a `Journal`.

